       <col style="width: 1176px">
      </colgroup>
      <tbody>
       <tr>
        <td>
         <p><strong>Send messages</strong></p>
        </td>
        <td>
         <p>Sending a message is quite similar to receiving messages. To send a message, the client needs to emit <a href="/chat/3.15/customer-channel-api#id-(3.15)CustomerChannelAPI-sendMessage" data-scope="internal">sendMessage </a>event with payload <a href="/chat/3.15/customer-channel-api#id-(3.15)CustomerChannelAPI-ChatMessageobject" data-scope="internal">ChatMessage </a>and <a href="/chat/3.15/customer-channel-api#id-(3.15)CustomerChannelAPI-ActivityMessageobject" data-scope="internal">ActivityMessage</a> as per need.</p>
        </td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
        <td>
         <p><strong>Receive messages</strong></p>
        </td>
        <td>
         <p>Client needs to implement <a href="/chat/3.15/customer-channel-api#id-(3.15)CustomerChannelAPI-messageArrived" data-scope="internal">Customer Channel API | id (3.15)CustomerChannelAPI messageArrived</a>&nbsp;event for the conversation. Payload for this event is a message. Message is the parent class of <a href="/chat/3.15/customer-channel-api#id-(3.15)CustomerChannelAPI-ChatMessageobject" data-scope="internal">ChatMessage </a>and <a href="/chat/3.15/customer-channel-api#id-(3.15)CustomerChannelAPI-ActivityMessageobject" data-scope="internal">ActivityMessage</a>. The payload contains property type in the JSON root, which can be either <a href="/chat/3.15/customer-channel-api#id-(3.15)CustomerChannelAPI-ChatMessageobject" data-scope="internal">ChatMessage</a> or <a href="/chat/3.15/customer-channel-api#id-(3.15)CustomerChannelAPI-ActivityMessageobject" data-scope="internal">ActivityMessage</a>.</p>
        </td>
       </tr>
      </tbody>
     </table>
    </div>
   </table-sort>
  </scroll-shadow>
 </table-expand>
</div>
